                             Backyard Conservation

           S.K. Worm answers your questions about soil and stuff!


   The Natural Resources Conservation Service (NRCS), formerly the Soil
   Conservation Service, is the federal agency that works hand-in-hand
   with the American people to conserve natural resources on private
   lands.  Using our scientific and technical expertise, and our
   partnerships with soil and water conservation districts and others, we
   help people conserve all natural resources on private lands.

   The Mississippi State Office is located at 100 West Capitol Street,
   Suite 1321, Jackson, Mississippi  39269.  Our telephone number is (601)
   965-5196.  The fax number is (601) 965-4940.

